  "text": "Salmonella requires siderophore synthesis in mice. Bacteria overproduce siderophores in strain backgrounds lacking siderophore import genes such as iroN and fepA [CITATION_1] . Excessive siderophore production could result in local iron starvation and thus poor tissue colonization in vivo. To determine whether the in vivo growth defects observed for the ⌬iroN and ⌬fepA strains reflected enhanced siderophore production, a strain unable to import or produce enterobactin and salmochelin (⌬iroN ⌬fepA ⌬entC) was generated. Mice orogastrically inoculated with individual wildtype or ⌬iroN ⌬fepA ⌬entC bacteria were sacrificed at 2 weeks postinfection, and tissue colonization was determined (Fig. 6) .",
